==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Preëxistence
<hw>Pre`⟦eum⟧x*ist"ence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Existence in a former state, or previous to something
else.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Wisdom declares her antiquity and <qex>pre⟦eum⟧xistence</qex> to
all the works of this earth.</q> <rj><qau>T. Burnet.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Existence of the soul before its union with the
body; -- a doctrine held by certain philosophers.</def>
<rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Preexistency</ent>⟦br⟧
